article_title: HMSA’s investments made up for premium revenue shortfall
article_text: Hawaii Medical Service Association’s investments bailed out the state’s largest health insurer last year after premium revenue fell short of covering health benefits, administrative expenses and costs associated with the Affordable Care Act.
